 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lmviu","title":"parity: add_path/add_cycle/add_star keyword parameter names","description":"NetworkX exposes add_path(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_path, **attr), add_cycle(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_cycle, **attr), and add_star(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_star, **attr). FNX currently names these parameters G and nodes, so documented keyword calls like fnx.add_path(G_to_add_to=G, nodes_for_path=[1,2]) raise TypeError. Align the public signatures while preserving positional behavior and add parity tests.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:20:06.172080189Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.168859030Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.167009410Z","close_reason":"Completed in 92bae80","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lz7u6","title":"parity: connectivity bridge_components missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components(G) returns 2-edge-connected components after removing bridges. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to nx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components via _networkx_graph_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:44:53.163889437Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:14:43.967902315Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:14:43.966070217Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in fnx — top-level export matches nx.connectivity exactly. Landed tests/python/test_connectivity_parity_extras.py (commit 3765516) with 37 cases freezing the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-m4msi","title":"parity: utils.random_sequence powerlaw_sequence + zipf_rv + cumulative_distribution + is_valid_tree_degree_sequence (4 functions)","description":"Four random-sequence utilities from networkx.utils.random_sequence not surfaced by franken_networkx: powerlaw_sequence(n, exponent=2.0, seed=None), zipf_rv(alpha, xmin=1, seed=None), cumulative_distribution(distribution), is_valid_tree_degree_sequence(degree_sequence). These are used by stochastic graph generators and degree-sequence sanity checks. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level and adding to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:59:39.857059179Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:18:46.320103675Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:18:46.318235318Z","close_reason":"Already implemented. powerlaw_sequence/zipf_rv/cumulative_distribution exposed at fnx top level matching nx.utils bit-for-bit when seeded; discrete_sequence on fnx.utils; is_valid_tree_degree_sequence is fnx-only ((bool, reason) tuple). Landed tests/python/test_random_sequence_parity.py (commit d2ed994) with 89 cases freezing the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-mnrem","title":"parity: fnx.approximation.* exposed (G, *args, **kwargs) catch-all signatures, hiding all real kwargs","description":"_ApproximationNamespace dynamically wrapped each approximation function as (G, *args, **kwargs), so inspect.signature(fnx.approximation.X) returned a useless catch-all for every function. nx exposes the documented per-function signatures (average_clustering(G, trials, seed), christofides(G, weight, tree), greedy_tsp(G, weight, source), etc). 27 functions affected. Drop-in callers couldn't see what kwargs are accepted via introspection, IDEs and type-checkers couldn't help, and typos passed silently into nx's **kwargs handling. Fix: functools.wraps(nx_func) on the wrapper so the original signature/name/docstring are preserved. 30 parity tests freeze the contract.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T04:41:51.191871760Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:41:51.191871760Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-ntkdn","title":"parity: random_sequence powerlaw/zipf/cumulative_distribution/is_valid_tree_degree_sequence (4 fns)","description":"Four random-sequence utilities from networkx.utils.random_sequence not surfaced: powerlaw_sequence(n, exponent=2.0, seed=None), zipf_rv(alpha, xmin=1, seed=None), cumulative_distribution(distribution), is_valid_tree_degree_sequence(degree_sequence). Used by stochastic generators and degree-seq sanity checks. Add wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T22:04:43.303897526Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T22:19:37.064336059Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T22:19:37.062433818Z","close_reason":"Shipped in b08418c: powerlaw_sequence/zipf_rv/cumulative_distribution/is_valid_tree_degree_sequence wrappers; all 4 verified against nx (n=20 exp=2.5 seed=42 powerlaw match exactly, cumulative_distribution = [0,0.5,0.8,1.0]).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-oiic9","title":"parity: all_pairs_node_connectivity flow_func ignored + iteration order","description":"fnx.all_pairs_node_connectivity(G, nbunch=None, flow_func=None) accepts flow_func but ignores it (always uses default max-flow). Also outer/inner dict iteration order differs from networkx for K4: fnx outer order is 1,0,2,3 while nx is 0,1,2,3. Honor flow_func by delegating to nx when provided, and stabilize iteration order (use G.nodes() insertion order). Located in python/franken_networkx/__init__.py near the existing all_pairs_node_connectivity wrapper.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T04:58:20.898200931Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:56.920452351Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:56.918586339Z","close_reason":"Completed in f14208d","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-qtbp2","title":"parity: node_link_data/node_link_graph accepted positional source/target (kwarg-only in nx)","description":"fnx.node_link_data(G, 'from_', 'to_') worked but nx requires source/target/name/key/edges/nodes as keyword-only (the public signature uses '*,'). Symmetric defect on node_link_graph. Drop-in callers writing for nx wouldn't notice; callers writing for fnx and switching to nx would hit a TypeError. Hardened both signatures with '*,' so positional usage is rejected identically. Added tests/python/test_node_link_kwarg_only_parity.py with 5 cases pinning the contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:22:28.512465018Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:23:11.384386337Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:23:11.381244470Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit b739569. node_link_data and node_link_graph now require source/target/name/key/edges/nodes as keyword-only (matching nx). 5 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
